nverse Kinematics, or CCDIK, to manipulate a chain of bones in a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Skeleton2D","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" so it reaches a defined target."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"CCDIK works by rotating a set of bones, typically called a “bone chain”, on a single axis. Each bone is rotated to face the target from the tip (by default), which over a chain of bones allow it to rotate properly to reach the target. Because the bones only rotate on a single axis, CCDIK ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"can"}]},{"text":" look more robotic than other IK solvers.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The CCDIK modifier has "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ccdik_joints"},{"type":"text","text":", which are the data objects that hold the data for each joint in the CCDIK chain. This is different from a bone! CCDIK joints hold the data needed for each bone in the bone chain used by CCDIK."}]}],"style":"note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"CCDIK also fully supports angle constraints, allowing for more control over how a solution is met.","type":"text"}]}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/SkeletonModification2DCCDIK","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"]]},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/skeletonmodification2dccdik"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[],"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Skeleton2D":{"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Skeleton2D"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Skeleton2D"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swift